.TH "CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontVariantCaps" "JS" "July 23, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontVariantCaps \- CanvasRenderingContext2D:
fontVariantCaps property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]CanvasRenderingContext2D.fontVariantCaps\f[B]\f[R]
property of the Canvas API specifies an alternative capitalization of
the rendered text.
.PP
This corresponds to the CSS \f[CR]font\-variant\-caps\f[R] property.
.SH VALUE
The font alternative capitalization value, which is one of:
.TP
\f[B]normal\f[R] (default)
Deactivates of the use of alternate glyphs.
.TP
\f[B]small\-caps\f[R]
Enables display of small capitals (OpenType feature: \f[CR]smcp\f[R]).
Small\-caps glyphs typically use the form of uppercase letters but are
reduced to the size of lowercase letters.
.TP
\f[B]all\-small\-caps\f[R]
Enables display of small capitals for both upper and lowercase letters
(OpenType features: \f[CR]c2sc\f[R], \f[CR]smcp\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]petite\-caps\f[R]
Enables display of petite capitals (OpenType feature: \f[CR]pcap\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]all\-petite\-caps\f[R]
Enables display of petite capitals for both upper and lowercase letters
(OpenType features: \f[CR]c2pc\f[R], \f[CR]pcap\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]unicase\f[R]
Enables display of mixture of small capitals for uppercase letters with
normal lowercase letters (OpenType feature: \f[CR]unic\f[R]).
.TP
\f[B]titling\-caps\f[R]
Enables display of titling capitals (OpenType feature: \f[CR]titl\f[R]).
Uppercase letter glyphs are often designed for use with lowercase
letters.
When used in all uppercase titling sequences they can appear too strong.
Titling capitals are designed specifically for this situation.
.PP
The property can be used to get or set the font capitalization value.
.PP
Note that there are accessibility concerns with some of these, which are
outlined in the corresponding \f[CR]font\-variant\-caps\f[R] topic.
.SH EXAMPLES
In this example we display the text \[lq]Hello World\[rq] using each of
the supported values of the \f[CR]fontVariantCaps\f[R] property.
The value is also displayed for each case by reading the property.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]canvas\f[R] id=\[dq]canvas\[dq] width=\[dq]700\[dq] height=\[dq]220\[dq]></\f[B]canvas\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] ctx = canvas.getContext(\[dq]2d\[dq]);
ctx.font = \[dq]20px serif\[dq];

\f[I]// Default (normal)\f[R]
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (default: ${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 20);

\f[I]// Capitalization: small\-caps\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]small\-caps\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 50);

\f[I]// Capitalization: all\-small\-caps\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]all\-small\-caps\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 80);

\f[I]// Capitalization: petite\-caps\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]petite\-caps\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 110);

\f[I]// Capitalization: all\-petite\-caps\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]all\-petite\-caps\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 140);

\f[I]// Capitalization: unicase\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]unicase\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 170);

\f[I]// Capitalization: titling\-caps\f[R]
ctx.fontVariantCaps = \[dq]titling\-caps\[dq];
ctx.fillText(\[ga]Hello world (${ctx.fontVariantCaps})\[ga], 5, 200);
.EE
